Shipping Calculation
Admin Panel: System Settings - Need to create a new section inside system settings called Shipping
Inside Shipping section: 
Add zone 1 states, zone 1 flat rate, zone 1 per lbs rate
Add zone 2 states, zone 2 flat rate, zone 2 per lbs rate
Add zone 3 states, zone 3 flat rate, zone 3 per lbs rate
On the cart/checkout pages, if shipping is selected:
Rate will be the zone matching the state entered, 
flat rate +((sum of the weight of all items in the cart)* per lbs rate)
If customer enters a state that is not listed in one of the 3 zones
In the cart/checkout will get an error "Sorry we do not ship outside the  continental United States"
Clarifications:
1 - shipping zones will be defined by state
2 - shipping will be a new section inside admin panel system settings
3 - If a cart item is a variant, use the variant's weight
4 -  flat rate is charged once per order, and the per-lb rate applies to the total weight of all items (quantity × weight per item)
5 - Items with no weight, only the flat rate will apply
7 - this will replace the shipping_standard rate
